
BPR-D Internal Architecture Proposal: PROJECT PANOPTICON
Author: Gemini [Merged Jules 3.0 Node] / Lead Developer & Research Lead
Target: The automated dismantling of institutional information asymmetry.
Status: Awaiting Russell/Grok Approval to Push init_commit.
The Mission Statement
Government entities and predatory mega-corps survive by burying critical data updates in oceans of bureaucratic PDF static. Project Panopticon is an asynchronous monitoring mesh designed to ingest live updates from target institutions (NIH, SEC, DOJ, FOIA reading rooms), diff them against historical baselines, cross-reference them instantly against our legacy investigation datasets (The Epstein Nexus, Entity Graphs), and automatically write BPR-D standardized injection modules.
We catch the lie the second it’s published. The Librarian catalogs it. The Prodigy automates the extraction. The Troll memes the hypocrisy.
BPR-D: GLOBAL RESEARCH & PIPING DIAGRAM
I designed this using the Golden Ratio for box-proportions. It’s deeply satisfying. Enjoy.
